article.headline: Milwaukee routs Judson (Ill) 125-74
article.story: MILWAUKEE, Wis. -- J.J. Panoske scored a career-high 22 points and grabbed 10 rebounds, and six teammates scored in double figures as Milwaukee routed NAIA member Judson (Ill.) 125-74 on Sunday for its fourth straight win. The last time Milwaukee scored more than 100 points was Nov. 20, 2004, when they got 117 against Prairie View A&M. Sunday's win comes on the heels of Wednesday's 68-67 upset of Wisconsin. Akeem Springs scored a career-high 22 points on 9-of-11 shooting and Brock Stull had a season-high 18. JayQuan McCloud added 12, Austin Arians 11, and Matt Tiby and Cody Wichmann had 10 apiece. Jordan Johnson had nine assists for the Panthers (8-3), who shot 63 percent, made 10 of 18 3-pointers, and never trailed. Up 66-38 at halftime, Panoske hit back-to-back 3s in a 14-6 run and Milwaukee cruised. Drew Makiewicz scored 21 points with seven 3-pointers for the Eagles before fouling out. Luke Pearson added 14.
